dct_title_s: Marine Protected Areas, Hopkins Marine Laboratory, California, 2000
dct_description_sm: This polygon shapefile depicts the (estimated) boundary of the Hopkins Marine Laboratory reserve located in Pacific Grove, California on the Monterey Peninsula. This layer is part of a collection of data created by the California Department of Fish and Game.
To identify the approximate area of the Hopkins Marine Lab reserve for mapping other kelp harvest areas and no-take MPAs along the Montery coast.
Estimated area of Hopkins Marine Lab. Not for definitive area calculations.
This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
